Distribution and habitat. The type-locality is a heavily karstic region with many sharp rock ridges and pinnacles (
Fig. 4
) forming a honeycombed landscape that makes field work difficult. Pine-oak forest covers the landscape and in some areas a moderate accumulation of leaf litter may be found in rock crevices. The slope of the type-locality is drained by the upper tributaries of the Río Atoyac, which is a tributary of the Río Verde.
